{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the interests of participants were slightly inclined to positive polarity on average (excluding making doggy bags available at restaurants).",
    "The aforementioned four UI conditions (chatbots) employed ChatGPT, OpenAI instruction-tuned LLM, via Azure OpenAI Service GPT API (gpt-3.5-turbo) to generate answers for participants' questions.",
    "In particular, we used an LLM promptengineering technique in the SUGGESTIVE, SUGGESTIVE ++, and EXPOSITIVE bots to complement additional information with plain answers for questions.",
    "One possible way in our proposed suggestive ending strategy in chatbots is to suggest perspectives for decision-making explicitly, such as key issues (Câmara et al., 2021; Petridis et al., 2023) and positive/negative aspects for themes (Liao and Fu, 2014; Liao et al., 2015).",
    "However, such explicit suggestions are revealing and do not encourage users to proactively reflect on what they should think for their decision-making."
  ]
}